1.1-4.2-2:
Procedure for implementing a Performance Improvement Plan (PIP)
Here are the steps I suggest for implementing a PIP: 1) Meet with that person to discuss your dissatisfaction with his/her performance;
2) Talk about facts and give examples that support your assessment of his/her performance;
3) Establish a written plan with specific and realistic goals that the person must achieve to meet your requirements;
4) Agree with him/her on how you will measure these goals. These should be quantifiable;

1.1-4.2-3:
Procedure for implementing a Performance Improvement Plan (PIP) (continued)
5) Decide together how long it will take to meet your goals. This time frame is usually calculated in months, not weeks. He/she must understand that if the goals are not met, you will have to terminate his/her employment;
6) Determine together the regular meetings that you will have with his/her in order to help his/her achieve the results you have requested;
7) Write the PIP agreed upon between you and have the person who needs to improve his/her performance sign it.
You have a sample PIP to help you in your writing (supplementary file).
